# Documentation

- Keep documentation practical, honest, and portfolio-friendly.
- Explain why the project exists and what it teaches.
- Include local quickstart steps and curl examples when endpoints are implemented.
- Use text or Mermaid diagrams when they clarify architecture.
- Keep docs synchronized with code and examples.
- Clearly label MVP features versus stretch goals.
- Avoid pretending this is production-ready.
- Document tradeoffs honestly.
- Add a `What I learned` section to the README as the project matures.
